snippet.textDisplay:
All those who continually criticise these businesses for not taking daylight robbery offers have zero understanding of how investment works. Dragons den is a reality show with inflated egos. They don't wave a magic wand. They can't open doors just on the drop of a hat. Many of the businesses that come on the show do so for promotion. Most of the investments never actually materialise. Dragons den is ostensibly an entertaining bit of fiction. I couldn't even describe it as a reality show.


What gets me is so few of you understand. I am staggered actually. The offer was derisory. This is a TV show. It isn't real life.
